            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "AS are the older Indian accounting standards notified in 2021 and applied by most private companies, while Ind AS are converged with IFRS and are mandatory for listed companies and large unlisted ones. Ind AS relies more on fair value and substance over form, so leases, financial instruments and revenue recognition are measured differently even when the underlying transaction is identical."
